content:
To create an aesthetically pleasing webpage that showcases the flower arrangement for a milestone birthday celebration, I'll guide you through the HTML structure and provide some basic styling with CSS. Additionally, I'll include a simple JavaScript function to calculate the total cost of the flower arrangement.

Here's a basic example of how you can structure the webpage:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Birthday Party Flower Arrangement</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            color: #333;
        }
        header {
            background-color: #ff6f61;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px 0;
            font-size: 2em;
        }
        .container {
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .image-section {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .image-section img {
            max-width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
        .image-section p {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        th, td {
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: left;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        }
        th {
            background-color: #ff6f61;
            color: white;
        }
        .total-cost {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 1.2em;
            text-align: right;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        Birthday Party Flower Arrangement
    </header>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="image-section">
            <img src="flower-arrangement.jpg" alt="Flower Arrangement">
            <p>An exquisite arrangement featuring roses, lilies, and daisies styled in a cascading design, inspired by the elegance of nature's bounty.</p>
        </div>
        <table>
            <tr>
                <th>Flower Type</th>
                <th>Quantity</th>
                <th>Price per Stem</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Roses</td>
                <td><input type="number" value="10" id="roses-quantity"></td>
                <td><input type="number" value="2.5" id="roses-price" step="0.01"></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Lilies</td>
                <td><input type="number" value="5" id="lilies-quantity"></td>
                <td><input type="number" value="3.0" id="lilies-price" step="0.01"></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Daisies</td>
                <td><input type="number" value="20" id="daisies-quantity"></td>
                <td><input type="number" value="1.0" id="daisies-price" step="0.01"></td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <div class="total-cost">
            Total Cost: $<span id="total-cost">0.00</span>
        </div>
        <button onclick="calculateTotal()">Calculate Total</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        function calculateTotal() {
            const rosesQuantity = parseFloat(document.getElementById('roses-quantity').value);
            const rosesPrice = parseFloat(document.getElementById('roses-price').value);
            const liliesQuantity = parseFloat(document.getElementById('lilies-quantity').value);
            const liliesPrice = parseFloat(document.getElementById('lilies-price').value);
            const daisiesQuantity = parseFloat(document.getElementById('daisies-quantity').value);
            const daisiesPrice = parseFloat(document.getElementById('daisies-price').value);

            const totalCost = (rosesQuantity * rosesPrice) + (liliesQuantity * liliesPrice) + (daisiesQuantity * daisiesPrice);

            document.getElementById('total-cost').textContent = totalCost.toFixed(2);
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Breakdown of Components:
- **Header:** Displays the title "Birthday Party Flower Arrangement" with a background color for emphasis.
- **Image Section:** Contains an image of the flower arrangement and a descriptive caption.
- **Table:** Lists the types of flowers, quantities, and prices with input fields allowing for interaction.
- **JavaScript Function:** Calculates the total cost based on user input from the table.

### Visual Styling:
- The webpage is styled using CSS for a clean and engaging look, with responsive elements.
- The header and table headers have a consistent color theme to maintain visual harmony.

This setup provides a user-friendly interface where users can explore the flower arrangement details and calculate costs dynamically.
